The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, August 30, 2003 				 Cop held for killing wife
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Burdwan, Aug. 29: A constable of the armed police was arrested by his colleagues from the district today and charged with burning his wife after her family failed to meet dowry demands.																								The police said Uttam Ankhure, 36, allegedly burnt Alo, 22, at his house in Raghunathpur in Budbud, about 180 km from Calcutta, last evening. Uttam was picked up after Alos father lodged a complaint with the police. His parents are absconding.																								Alos father Madan said he had paid Rs 2 lakh when she was married to the policeman two years ago. Uttam wanted more. He had returned home from his posting in Chinsurah on Thursday.
